//Paravertebral muscles

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select C1 to T4 vertebras from the localizer of Page 01 of Spine MRI
And	I'm on Page 08 of Spine MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Paravertebral muscles' from Finding dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Characterization I' tab is enabled and preselected
And 'Characterization II' tab is enabled

When I select 'Characterization I' tab
Then 'Longissimus capitis muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Levator scapulae muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Semispinalis colli muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Semispinalis capitis muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Splenius capitis muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Trapezius muscle' checkbox is enabled

And 'Erector spinae muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Quadratus lumborum muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Psoas major muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Multifidus muscle' checkbox is enabled

And 'Proximal enthesis' radio button is enabled
And 'Proximal musculotendinous junction' radio button is enabled
And 'Proximal third' radio button is enabled
And 'Middle third' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Erector spinae muscle' checkbox
Then 'Iliocostalis muscle' checkbox is enabled
And 'Longissimus muscle' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Muscle lesion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hematoma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fatty degeneration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Muscle hypertrophy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Muscle atrophy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Apophysitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fascial rupture' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Muscle lesion' checkbox
Then 'Muscle edema' radio button is enabled
And 'Muscle fiber tear (Type IIIa)' radio button is enabled
And 'Muscle-bundle tear (Type IIIb)' radio button is enabled
And 'Muscle tear / tendon tear (Type IV)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Muscle fiber tear (Type IIIa)' radio button
Then 'Diameter of rupture < 5 mm' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Muscle-bundle tear (Type IIIb)' radio button
Then 'Diameter of rupture â‰¥ 5 mm' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Muscle tear / tendon tear (Type IV)' radio button
Then 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Wavy appearance of the fibers' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osseous avulsion' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Retraction' checkbox
Then 'Retraction' input field is enabled

When I select 'Osseous avulsion' checkbox
Then 'Intracortical edema' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Hematoma' checkbox
Then 'Intramuscularly' checkbox is enabled
And 'Interfascial' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intermuscular' checkbox is enabled
And 'T1w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'Hyperacute' radio button is enabled
And 'Acute' radio button is enabled
And 'Subacute' radio button is enabled
And 'Chronic, organised' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Muscle atrophy' checkbox
Then 'Complete' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Fascial rupture' checkbox
Then 'Muscle hernia' checkbox is enabled
